tc.\r\n5) Upon visiting India - given even allegations (although false and unfounded) can result in non-bailable jail time till the process is concluded in court - Can I be detained if I visit India - seeking precautions and safety advice as an Australian citizen with essentially no Links in India other than this marriage.\r\n6) Will you be able to assist in helping the Husband in navigating this matter while collaborating with an Indian Legal Representative? You will also need to help me source a competent Indian Legal Representative.\r\nCONTEXT\r\n1) During the time of marriage Q1 2018 - Husband was an Australian citizen (No ID in India except for OCI) - wife was an Indian citizen.\r\n2) Marriage Certificate was obtained in India\r\n3) Partner visa applied in Australia by husband. Relationship issues ensued, husband withdrew the application. Wife accused (unfounded and false) DV (no substantiation - home affairs is non-judicial process) to get her permanent residency VISA - Wife obtained it in 2023\r\n4) Husband and Wife are living separately since June 2022. The acute time of relationship breakdown. Started much earlier. Wife was falsely accusing husband and family of many allegations to husbands friends and family + Indian charity ISC (Indian Support Center) since DEC 2021.\r\n5) Unknown if Wife has obtained Australian Citizenship\r\n6) Wife has sent email to me with false allegations of abuse/desertion etc. and asking for a mutual divorce if not she threatens court proceedings with above allegations. Asking for personal details (to serve court documents). Last week.\r\n7) Above actions seems out of the blue as couple were in a phase of reconciliation since Q3 2024 (still living separately). She supposedly went to visit her family in India. Calls were being declined. Then suddenly this email was sent. \r\n8) Wife followed up with WhatsApp messages, got ISC to reach out via email and tried to contact extended family - asking for husband person details for serving of court orders.\r\n9) Husband has not responded to anything. He is in a state of pain/sadness/disdain but also fears for consequences having heard the Indian Judicial system\'s biases etc. Wishes to Seek legal advice in Australia before doing so.</span> <p class=\"text-semi-light-grey col-v-1\">@ 12:30 PM-1:00 PM</p></div>', '2025-05-12 01:54:17', '2025-05-12 01:54:17', 'scheduled an paid appointment', NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
