(3, 'main', NULL, 'Criminal Law', 'criminal-law', NULL, NULL, 1, '<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><span style=\"font-size:15.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Georgia&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\"><span style=\"color:#1b4d89\">Criminal Law</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><span style=\"font-size:9.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\"><span style=\"color:#666666\">Are you facing assault charges in Australia but don&rsquo;t know the legal rights for your opinion to save your future. Don&rsquo;t worry Bansal Lawyers, help you to provide Expert Criminal Law Services in Melbourne, Australia.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><span style=\"font-size:9.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\"><span style=\"color:#666666\">If you have been charged with assault in Australia then you have to take a professional legal help immediately. Assault charges in Australia is very serious crime which has long term effect on your life that create a criminal record which make trouble to find a job, got travel restriction with visa cancelation for some countries also. </span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><span style=\"font-size:9.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\"><span style=\"color:#666666\">At Bansal Lawyers, our best criminal lawyers with knowledge and experience to deal with these type of cases provides you the best legal help and guidance throughout the process. Whatever you have been charged with normal assault, Assault charges which include actual body harm or more series offence with grievous body harm, we provide a free consultation to discuss on clients case. </span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Georgia&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\"><span style=\"color:#1b4d89\">Your Rights and the Prosecution&rsquo;s Burden of Proof</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><span style=\"font-size:9.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\"><span style=\"color:#666666\">In Australia, the legal system upholds the principle of innocent until proven guilty. The prosecution lawyer from the authority must need to prove the charges against you with strong and clear evidence which shows that you committed the offence without any reasonable concerns.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Georgia&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\"><span style=\"color:#1b4d89\">Types of Assault Charges in Australia</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"color:#333333\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:8.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Common Assault:</span></span></strong><span style=\"font-size:8.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">&nbsp;Physical contact without consent, typically without causing bodily harm.</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"color:#333333\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:8.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Assault Occasioning Actual Bodily Harm (ABH):</span></span></strong><span style=\"font-size:8.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">&nbsp;Causes injury to another person.</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"color:#333333\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:8.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Assault Occasioning Grievous Bodily Harm (GBH):</span></span></strong><span style=\"font-size:8.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">&nbsp;Involves serious or life-threatening injuries.</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><span style=\"font-size:9.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\"><span style=\"color:#666666\">In some cases multiple charges filed for the same incident in order to secure to find guilty by the court for at least one offence.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Georgia&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\"><span style=\"color:#1b4d89\">Where Will Your Assault Case Be Heard?</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><span style=\"font-size:9.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\"><span style=\"color:#666666\">The court where your assault case is heard depends on the severity of the charge and the laws in the state or territory where the offence occurred. Minor assault charges are typically dealt with in Magistrates Courts or Local Courts, while more serious cases, such as ABH or GBH, may be heard in higher courts like District, County, or Supreme Courts.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Georgia&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\"><span style=\"color:#1b4d89\">Factors Affecting the Seriousness of Your Assault Charges</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"color:#333333\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><span style=\"font-size:8.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Extent of injuries caused to the victim</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"color:#333333\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><span style=\"font-size:8.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Use of a weapon or threat of violence</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"color:#333333\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><span style=\"font-size:8.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Location of the offence (e.g., in the presence of children or at the victim&rsquo;s home)</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"color:#333333\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><span style=\"font-size:8.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">The victim&#39;s role (such as a police officer or emergency worker)</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"color:#333333\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><span style=\"font-size:8.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Your criminal history and whether the offence was premeditated or impulsive</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Georgia&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\"><span style=\"color:#1b4d89\">Penalties for Assault Offences in Australia</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"color:#333333\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:8.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Common Assault:</span></span></strong><span style=\"font-size:8.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">&nbsp;Up to 2 years&rsquo; imprisonment.</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"color:#333333\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:8.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Assault Occasioning Actual Bodily Harm (ABH):</span></span></strong><span style=\"font-size:8.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">&nbsp;Up to 5 years&rsquo; imprisonment, or 7 years if committed with others.</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"color:#333333\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:8.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Grievous Bodily Harm (GBH):</span></span></strong><span style=\"font-size:8.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">&nbsp;Up to 25 years&rsquo; imprisonment, depending on intent and whether the offence was committed with recklessness or deliberate harm.</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:9.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\"><span style=\"color:#666666\">Disclaimer:</span></span></span></strong><span style=\"font-size:9.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\"><span style=\"color:#666666\">&nbsp;This content is intended to provide general information about assault charges in Australia and is not a substitute for legal advice. The laws surrounding assault can vary by state and territory, and the outcome of any case will depend on its specific circumstances. For tailored legal advice, please contact our team of expert lawyers.</span></span></span></span></span></p>', 'Best Criminal Law Services in Melbourne &amp; Australia | Bansal Lawyers', 'Looking for expert criminal law services in Melbourne &amp; Australia? ? Bansal\r\nLawyers provides top-rated legal representation for all criminal cases. Contact\r\nus today for a consultation!', 'Protect your rights with experienced criminal law lawyers in Melbourne, Australia. Bansal Lawyers specialises in criminal defense, legal representation, and tailored advice. Contact us today!', NULL, NULL, '2024-12-27 19:00:06', '2025-03-14 00:26:25', 'other', 1),
(4, 'main', NULL, 'Family Law', 'family-law', NULL, NULL, 1, '<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\"><span style=\"color:#333333\">Your Guide to Separation, Parenting, and Property Settlements</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><span style=\"font-size:18.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\"><span style=\"color:#333333\">Family Law in Australia</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\"><span style=\"color:#333333\">At Bansal Lawyers, we always focus on family law in Australia. That I why we offer the best expert legal advice to help the client and their families rights. Our team will provide support to the clients for dealing and separation over parenting disputes, and also in property settlements. If you are married or in de facto relationship, Our team of best lawyers in Australia, is here to help you to get positive outcome and always try to make understand the family law in Australia.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\"><span style=\"color:#333333\">Overview of Family Law in Australia</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\"><span style=\"color:#333333\">What is family law in Australia? </span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\"><span style=\"color:#333333\">Family law in Australia is a governed primarily by the family law act 1975, which implement across the nation. In western Australia has it&rsquo;s own legal framework for de facto relationships, it a commonwealth system that applies to all married couples. In WA, de facto couples. In West Australia, couples who are in de facto relationship must clear the property and parenting disputes through law under the state, while if you are a married couple you have to follow the national Family Law System.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\"><span style=\"color:#333333\">In Western Australia Family court is the only on court which handling family law matters in the state, other side across Australia, cases related to family law are deal by the Family Court Australia and Federal Circuit Court of Australia.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\"><span style=\"color:#333333\">What are the key areas of Family Law.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\"><span style=\"color:#333333\">Separation and Divorce</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:24px; text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\"><span style=\"color:#333333\">Marriage: In Australia, People get divorce on no-fault basis like no need to prove that you are in wrong doing infidelity. After the 12 months of separation, you can apply for a divorce. For marriage with time less than 2 years, couples must be required to attend the counseling with meditation before filing for divorce, until any family violence is involved.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:24px; text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\"><span style=\"color:#333333\">De facto Relationships: Living with your partner in Australia from past 2 years, you considered as a de facto relationship. When you get separation in de facto relationships don&rsquo;t required a normal divorce until children and property got involved. </span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ol start=\"2\">\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\"><span style=\"color:#333333\">Parenting Arrangements</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:48px; text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\"><span style=\"color:#333333\">After separation in Australia after divorce, you will get one thing better to know that the court first consider the child where want to go with. Parents must reach the agreement about important matters about child primary considerations such as:</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\"><span style=\"color:#333333\">Children Living Arrangement</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\"><span style=\"color:#333333\">Schooling and Education</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\"><span style=\"color:#333333\">Time Spent with Family Members</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\"><span style=\"color:#333333\">Medical care and Treatment</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\"><span style=\"color:#333333\">Had to make informal agreements (verbal and written), by the Parents, or Provide these arrangements through the consent orders, which are legal and valid by the court. If both parents cannot reach the agreement process, will able to required for attend the meditation before the appearing the court for considers the case. </span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\"><span style=\"color:#333333\">3 Child Support</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\"><span style=\"color:#333333\">Child support means to make the children future secure with contributing financial help for their children. Parents help to manage child support payment through:</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\"><span style=\"color:#333333\">Parents get to manage self manage agreements</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\"><span style=\"color:#333333\">Register Assessment based on income and care arrangements through service Australia</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\"><span style=\"color:#333333\">Courts orders for typical cases related to the children who are above then 18 years</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ol start=\"3\">\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\"><span style=\"color:black\">Property Settlement</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:24px\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\"><span style=\"color:black\">It is necessary to know that how the divide assets and debts after separation. If you are married or in de facto relationship, you must be filed property settlement applications:</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:24px\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\"><span style=\"color:black\">If you are married have to submit property settlement within 12 months of divorce</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:24px\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\"><span style=\"color:black\">If you are de facto couples have to submit property settlement within 2 years of sepration</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\"><span style=\"color:#333333\">Settlements can be reached informally, formalized through Consent Orders, or determined by the court if no agreement is made. Courts consider contributions (financial and non-financial) and future needs (such as health and care responsibilities).</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\"><span style=\"color:black\">5. Spousal Maintenance</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\"><span style=\"color:#333333\">Spousal maintenance may be required if one partner is unable to support themselves after separation. The court considers factors like age, health, income, and the financial impact of the relationship when deciding on maintenance obligations.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\"><span style=\"color:black\">6. Family Dispute Resolution (Mediation)</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\"><span style=\"color:#333333\">Mediation is a vital step in resolving family law disputes, especially for parenting and property matters. Before seeking court intervention, parties are often encouraged to attend Family Dispute Resolution (FDR) to try to reach a mutually acceptable solution. If mediation fails, the court may require a Section 60I Certificate, allowing the case to proceed to court.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\"><span style=\"color:#333333\">Why Choose Bansal Lawyers for Your Family Law Matters?</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\"><span style=\"color:#333333\">At Bansal Lawyers, we understand that family law issues can be emotionally challenging and legally complex. Our experienced family lawyers are here to guide you through the entire process, whether you are dealing with separation, divorce, property settlements, or parenting disputes. We provide personalized legal advice tailored to your situation, ensuring the best possible outcome for you and your family.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\"><span style=\"color:#333333\">Contact Bansal Lawyers Today</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\"><span style=\"color:#333333\">If you&#39;re facing a family law issue, don&rsquo;t navigate it alone. Contact Bansal Lawyers today to schedule a consultation with our experienced family law team. We are dedicated to helping you resolve your family law matters efficiently, with empathy and expertise.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"/understanding-de-facto-relationship-vs-marriage-australia\">\r\n  Read about the differences between de facto relationships and marriage in Australia\r\n</a>', 'Best Family Lawyers in Australia | Family Law Experts in Melbourne', 'Looking for the best family lawyers in Australia? At Bansal Lawyers, we specialize in family\r\nlaw in Australia, offering expert legal advice and representation in Melbourne. Contact us\r\ntoday for a consultation!', 'Resolve family matters with compassionate and expert legal guidance from Bansal Lawyers in Melbourne, Australia. Specializing in divorce, child custody, and property settlements. Contact us today!', NULL, NULL, '2024-12-27 19:26:01', '2025-07-11 20:36:37', 'other', 1),
(5, NULL, NULL, 'Corporate Law', 'corporate-law', NULL, NULL, 1, '<div class=\"content-section\"><!-- Heading of the page included in the content section -->\r\n<h1>Corporate Law</h1>\r\n\r\n<p>Your Guide to Business Formation, Governance, and Dispute Resolution</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Corporate Law Experts in Australia</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>At Bansal Lawyers, we provide expert corporate law services to businesses of all sizes across Australia. Whether you&#39;re a startup, small business, or multinational corporation, our team of experienced corporate lawyers is here to guide you through corporate governance, compliance, transactions, and dispute resolution. We focus on ensuring your business stays compliant with Australian regulations while achieving its commercial goals.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>What is Corporate Law?</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Corporate law governs the formation, operation, and management of businesses. It includes corporate governance, ensuring businesses meet legal requirements, protecting shareholder interests, managing risks, and assisting with commercial transactions. It also involves dispute resolution for businesses facing conflicts.<br />\r\nIn Australia, the Corporations Act 2001 (Cth) is the primary legislation regulating companies. Corporate lawyers ensure businesses meet their legal obligations under this Act, helping ensure long-term success.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Our Corporate Law Expertise</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Business Formation &amp; Structuring:</strong> Helping with company registration and advising on the best structure for your business (e.g., partnerships, trusts, companies).</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Corporate Governance:</strong> Ensuring that directors and officers fulfill their legal duties and comply with corporate governance laws.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Mergers &amp; Acquisitions (M&amp;A):</strong> Providing expert legal advice on M&amp;A transactions, including due diligence, contract negotiation, and regulatory compliance.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Contract Drafting &amp; Review:</strong> Assisting with drafting and reviewing essential business contracts such as shareholder agreements, joint ventures, and supplier contracts.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Regulatory Compliance:</strong> Advising on compliance with ASIC regulations, financial reporting, and industry-specific laws.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Shareholder &amp; Partnership Disputes:</strong> Resolving disputes through mediation, arbitration, or litigation.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Employment Law:</strong> Offering advice on employment contracts, workplace disputes, and employment law compliance.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Intellectual Property (IP):</strong> Helping protect business assets like trademarks, patents, and copyrights.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Franchise Law:</strong> Advising on franchise agreements, franchisee compliance, and dispute resolution.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Insolvency &amp; Restructuring:</strong> Supporting businesses with insolvency issues, including debt recovery, liquidations, and voluntary administrations.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Why You Need a Corporate Lawyer</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>An experienced corporate lawyer can help your business:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Navigate complex legal frameworks and regulatory requirements.</li>\r\n	<li>Draft enforceable contracts that protect your interests and minimize disputes.</li>\r\n	<li>Safeguard intellectual property (IP) and valuable business assets.</li>\r\n	<li>Resolve disputes quickly to avoid disruption.</li>\r\n	<li>Ensure compliance with evolving laws and regulations, avoiding penalties and reputational harm.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Corporate Litigation and Dispute Resolution</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Disputes can arise in any business, whether related to contracts, shareholders, or regulatory issues. Our corporate litigation services include:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Contract Disputes: Resolving breaches of contract and other commercial disagreements.</li>\r\n	<li>Director &amp; Shareholder Disputes: Resolving conflicts between directors and shareholders, including issues of breach of duty and shareholder rights.</li>\r\n	<li>Fraud &amp; Misrepresentation: Taking legal action for fraud, misrepresentation, and wrongful acts.</li>\r\n	<li>Debt Recovery &amp; Insolvency: Assisting businesses with debt recovery and resolving insolvency-related disputes.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>We aim to resolve disputes quickly using alternative dispute resolution (ADR) methods like mediation and arbitration. If needed, we also offer court representation to protect your business interests.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Corporate Compliance and Risk Management</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Compliance with corporate laws is critical to avoiding legal risks. We support businesses with:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Corporate Governance Audits: Conducting audits to ensure your business complies with best practices and legal requirements.</li>\r\n	<li>ASIC Reporting &amp; Compliance: Guiding businesses through ASIC compliance, reporting requirements, and regulatory filings.</li>\r\n	<li>Workplace Health &amp; Safety Compliance: Ensuring compliance with workplace safety laws to prevent legal risks.</li>\r\n	<li>Anti-Money Laundering (AML) &amp; Counter-Terrorism Financing (CTF): Helping businesses meet AML and CTF obligations.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Why Choose Bansal Lawyers?</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>At Bansal Lawyers, we pride ourselves on:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Expertise:</strong> Our corporate lawyers have extensive experience across various industries and business sizes.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Tailored Solutions:</strong> We offer customized legal strategies that align with your business goals.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Client-Centered Approach:</strong> Your success is our priority. We work closely with you to achieve the best legal outcomes.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Competitive Pricing:</strong> We offer high-quality legal services at competitive rates, ensuring excellent value for your investment.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Contact Us Today</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>For expert advice on corporate law matters, contact Bansal Lawyers today. Our team is ready to guide you through your business&#39;s legal needs and help you make informed, confident decisions.</p>\r\n</div>', 'Corporate Litigation Lawyers in Melbourne | Bansal Lawyers', 'Need expert corporate litigation lawyers in Melbourne? Bansal Lawyers – trusted legal experts for business disputes, shareholder conflicts, contract breaches &amp; more.', 'Expert corporate litigation lawyers in Melbourne', NULL, NULL, '2024-12-27 19:28:07', '2025-07-12 15:43:15', 'other', 1),
(6, NULL, NULL, 'Personal Injury Law', 'personal-law', NULL, NULL, 1, '<div class=\"content-section\">\r\n<h1>Personal Injury Law</h1>\r\n\r\n<p>Your Guide to Seeking Compensation for Personal Injuries in Australia</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Personal Injury Law Services Across Australia</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Personal injury law in Australia is designed to provide compensation for individuals who have been injured due to the negligence or wrongful actions of others. Whether it&rsquo;s a car accident, workplace injury, medical negligence, or a slip-and-fall incident, personal injury law ensures that victims have access to justice and the financial support they need to recover and move forward with their lives.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>How We Can Help</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>At Bansal Lawyers, our team of experienced personal injury lawyers is dedicated to helping you navigate the legal process. We offer expert advice, represent you in claims, and ensure that you receive the compensation you deserve. Our lawyers will work tirelessly to investigate the circumstances surrounding your injury, gather evidence, and negotiate with insurance companies or represent you in court if necessary.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Types of Personal Injury Claims</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Personal injury claims in Australia cover a wide range of situations where someone&rsquo;s negligence or carelessness has caused harm. Some of the most common types of personal injury claims include:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Motor Vehicle Accidents:</strong> Injuries sustained in car, motorcycle, or pedestrian accidents.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Workplace Injuries:</strong> Injuries occurring in the workplace due to employer negligence or unsafe working conditions.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Medical Negligence:</strong> Injuries caused by the failure of medical professionals to meet accepted standards of care.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Public Liability:</strong> Injuries occurring on public or private property due to hazardous conditions.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Product Liability:</strong> Injuries caused by defective or unsafe products.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Slip and Fall Accidents:</strong> Injuries that happen when a person slips, trips, or falls due to unsafe conditions.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Eligibility for Compensation</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>To be eligible for compensation in a personal injury case, certain criteria must be met. This generally includes proving that:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>The injury was caused by the negligence or fault of another party.</li>\r\n	<li>Your injury is serious enough to warrant a claim.</li>\r\n	<li>In most cases, you must lodge a claim within a specific time frame (typically 3 years from the date of the injury).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Our lawyers will assess your case in detail to determine the best course of action and help you gather the evidence needed to strengthen your claim.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>What Can You Claim?</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>If you have been injured due to someone else&rsquo;s negligence, you may be entitled to compensation for:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Medical Expenses:</strong> Costs related to the treatment and rehabilitation of your injury.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Lost Wages:</strong> Compensation for the income you have lost due to your inability to work.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Pain and Suffering:</strong> Compensation for the physical pain and emotional distress caused by your injury.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Future Care Costs:</strong> If your injury will require ongoing care or assistance, you may be entitled to compensation for future medical needs.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Loss of Enjoyment of Life:</strong> If your injury significantly affects your quality of life, compensation may be available for the loss of your ability to enjoy everyday activities.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>The Personal Injury Claim Process in Australia</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The process of making a personal injury claim typically involves the following steps:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li><strong>Consultation:</strong> Meet with one of our lawyers for an initial consultation to assess the merits of your case.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Investigation:</strong> Our team will gather all the necessary evidence, including medical records, witness statements, and accident reports.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Negotiation:</strong> We will negotiate with the insurance company or responsible party to reach a fair settlement.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Litigation:</strong> If a fair settlement cannot be reached, we will take the case to court to seek justice for you.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3>Why Choose Bansal Lawyers for Personal Injury Claims?</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Expertise:</strong> We have a track record of successfully handling a wide range of personal injury cases in Australia.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>No Win, No Fee:</strong> We offer a no-win, no-fee service, meaning you don&rsquo;t pay us unless we win your case.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Personalised Service:</strong> We provide tailored advice and legal representation that focuses on your unique needs and circumstances.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Compassionate Lawyers:</strong> We understand the emotional and financial strain that comes with a personal injury, and we are here to support you every step of the way.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Transparent Advice:</strong> We offer honest and realistic advice, so you are always informed about the status of your case.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>', 'Personal Law Services in Melbourne, Australia |Wills, Estate Planning & Disputes |Bansal Lawyers', 'Deals in personal legal matters with ease. Bansal Lawyers in Melbourne, Australia, specializes in wills, estate planning, and dispute resolution. Trusted legal support tailored to your needs. Contact us today!', 'Deals in personal legal matters with ease. Bansal Lawyers in Melbourne, Australia, specializes in wills, estate planning, and dispute resolution. Trusted legal support tailored to your needs. Contact us today!', NULL, NULL, '2024-12-27 19:29:54', '2025-01-07 21:16:56', 'other', 1);
