div style=\"margin-bottom:11px; text-align:center\">\r\n<hr /></div>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong>Why Choose Bansal Lawyers for Your ART Appeal?</strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong>Deep Knowledge of Australian Migration Law</strong><br />\r\n	We have strong grasp of challenging visa process legal guidelines and wide experience working through the ART process.</span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong>Higher Chances of Success</strong><br />\r\n	Legal representation considerably boosts the opportunities of a desired outcome. Our record of success with ART speaks for itself.</span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong>Value-Driven Service</strong><br />\r\n	Where as legal representation includes costs, our service is a smart use of money that could save your effort and time, lessen stress, and prevent further legal hurdles down the track.</span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"margin-bottom:11px; text-align:center\">\r\n<hr /></div>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong>Need Help with Your ART Appeal? Let Bansal Lawyers Guide You.</strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Whether you&#39;re challenging a <strong>student visa cancellation</strong>, <strong>partner visa refusal</strong>, or any other type of immigration decision, <strong>Bansal Lawyers</strong> is here to provide trusted legal representation and results-driven advocacy.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;,sans-serif\">?</span> <strong>Call us today</strong> or <span style=\"font-family:&quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;,sans-serif\">?</span> <strong>Book a consultation online</strong> to discuss your AAT appeal options with our expert immigration lawyers.</span></span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.bansallawyers.com.au/how-to-appeal-visa-refusal-administrative-review-tribunal\" title=\"How to Appeal Visa Refusal – Administrative Review Tribunal\">How to Appeal a Visa Refusal through the Administrative Review Tribunal </a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"/student-visa-refusal-bias-jaggi-v-minister-2024\">Read about the Jaggi v Minister [2024] case involving student visa refusal due to bias </a></p>', 'Visa Refusal Appeal Help – AAT Review Lawyers in Melbourne', 'Challenging a visa refusal? Our experienced Immigration lawyers in Melbourne assist with AAT (Administrative Appeals Tribunal) applications for reviews.', 'AAT appeal lawyers, Administrative Appeals Tribunal, visa refusal review, migration appeal legal help, visa reconsideration, Immigration lawyers in Melbourne', NULL, NULL, '2025-01-16 22:35:13', '2025-07-19 17:20:18', 'other', 1),
(27, 'sub', 7, 'Visa Refusals/Visa Cancellation', 'visa-refusals-visa-cancellation', 'Visa_Refusals.png', 'Visa Refusals/Visa Cancellation', 1, '<div class=\"content-section\"><!-- Heading of the page included in the content section -->\r\n<h1>Visa Refusals/Visa Cancellation</h1>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Visa Refusal</span></span></strong></span></span></p>\r\n<a href=\"/student-visa-refusal-bias-jaggi-v-minister-2024\">Read about Student visa refusal bias jaggi v minister 2024</a>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Visa refusal occurs when the Department of Home Affairs or the relevant immigration authorities deny an applicant the right to enter, stay, or remain in Australia. There are many reasons why a visa might be refused, including:</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Failure to meet visa criteria</span></span></strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">: Each visa category has specific requirements, and failure to meet these criteria could lead to a refusal.</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Character issues</span></span></strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">: If the applicant does not meet the character requirements set out by Australian law, their visa may be refused.</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Health-related concerns</span></span></strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">: Applicants who fail the health assessment may face refusal.</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"/how-to-appeal-visa-refusal-cancellation-art\">Read about How to appeal visa refusal cancellation art</a></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Inaccurate or incomplete information</span></span></strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">: Providing false information or incomplete documentation can result in a visa refusal.</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Visa history</span></span></strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">: A history of visa violations or overstaying in Australia can also be a factor.</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Visa Cancellation</span></span></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Visa cancellation refers to the revocation of an individual&rsquo;s visa by the Australian government after it has been granted. This can occur at any point during an individual&rsquo;s stay in Australia and can be triggered for various reasons, including:</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Non-compliance with visa conditions</span></span></strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">: Violating the conditions of the visa, such as working without authorization, studying without the proper visa, or overstaying the visa period.</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Criminal conduct</span></span></strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">: If a visa holder is convicted of a serious crime or engages in behaviour deemed detrimental to Australian society, their visa may be cancelled.</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">False information or fraud</span></span></strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">: If a visa holder is found to have provided false information in their visa application, it could lead to visa cancellation.</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Health or character issues</span></span></strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">: If the visa holder&rsquo;s health or character is found to be incompatible with the visa requirements, the Department of Home Affairs may cancel the visa.</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">How Bansal Lawyers Can Help</span></span></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">If your visa has been refused or cancelled, our experienced migration lawyers at Bansal Lawyers can help you understand your options and, where appropriate, challenge the decision. Our team can assist you in the following ways:</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt; margin-left:24px; padding:0in 0in 1.0pt 0in\">\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Providing expert legal advice</span></span></strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">: We offer guidance on whether you are eligible for another visa or if other remedies are available under Australian immigration law.</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Reviewing visa refusal or cancellation decisions</span></span></strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">: Our team will carefully review the reasons for refusal or cancellation to ensure all factors are considered.</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Appealing a refusal or cancellation</span></span></strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">: We can help file an appeal with the Administrative Review Tribunal (ART) or represent you in court if necessary.</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"/how-to-appeal-visa-refusal-administrative-review-tribunal\">Read about How to appeal visa refusal administrative review tribunal</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"/chikweu-v-minister-2024-federal-court-visa-refusal-overturn\">Read about Chikweu v minister 2024 federal court visa refusal overturn</a></p>', 'Appeal Visa Refusal or Cancellation in Australia | Bansal Lawyers', 'Overcome visa refusals & cancellations with Bansal Lawyers. Get legal advice for AAT appeals & ministerial intervention applications', 'Visa refusal lawyers Melbourne, visa cancellation appeal, AAT visa rejection, ministerial intervention, immigration legal help', NULL, NULL, '2025-01-16 22:36:06', '2025-07-11 22:36:16', 'other', 1),
(28, 'sub', 7, 'Federal Court Application', 'federal-court-application', 'federal_court_application.png', 'Federal Court Application', 1, '<div class=\"content-section\"><!-- Heading of the page included in the content section -->\r\n<h1>Federal Court Application</h1>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">When to Apply to the Federal Court</span></span></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">If you have received an adverse decision from the Administrative Review Tribunal (ART) regarding your visa, you may be able to appeal the decision to the <strong>Federal Court</strong>. This typically occurs when:</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">The decision involves a <strong>jurisdictional error</strong>, as discussed earlier.</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">The decision is based on incorrect interpretation or application of the Migration Act or Migration Regulations.</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">There are issues of law that need clarification by the higher court.</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">A <strong>Federal Court application</strong> is a serious legal step and is typically sought when the individual has exhausted all other review options, such as the ART application. In some cases, the Federal Circuit and Family Court of Australia may have jurisdiction and can be a more cost-effective option.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:14.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Who Is Involved in a Court Case?</span></span></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">In legal proceedings, the people involved are called parties. The main parties in a case are:<br />\r\n&bull; <strong>Applicant</strong>: If you apply to the Court to start a matter, you are called the applicant. If you are starting an appeal, you are called the appellant.<br />\r\n&bull; <strong>Respondent</strong>: If a case is brought against you, you are the respondent (or defendant in certain matters).<br />\r\n&bull; <strong>Self-represented litigant</strong>: If you represent yourself in the case without a lawyer, you are treated as a self-represented litigant.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">What Forms Do I Need?</span></span></strong><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">To start a matter in the Federal Court, you need to prepare an application form. The most commonly used form is Form 15 - Originating Application. Depending on your case, you may need additional supporting documents such as an affidavit (Form 59) or a statement of claim (Form 17).<br />\r\nSome cases may require a Genuine Steps Statement (Form 16), which outlines the steps taken to resolve the dispute before starting the court process.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">How Do I Submit My Documents?</span></span></strong><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Once you have completed the necessary forms and documents, you need to lodge them with the Court. This can be done in several ways:<br />\r\n&bull; <strong>Elodgement via the Court&rsquo;s online system</strong>.<br />\r\n&bull; <strong>Submitting in person at a local Registry</strong>.<br />\r\n&bull; <strong>Mailing or faxing the documents</strong>.<br />\r\nOnce the documents are lodged and accepted, they will be filed, and you will receive a Notice of Filing confirming the submission.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">What Happens After Filing My Application?</span></span></strong><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Once your documents are filed correctly, the Court will issue a Notice of Filing and Hearing which includes the date and time of the first hearing. This confirms that the Court has accepted the documents and your case will proceed.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">How Do I Serve Documents on Other Parties?</span></span></strong><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">After filing, you must serve copies of your application on the other party. You can do this by:<br />\r\n&bull; Personally delivering the documents.<br />\r\n&bull; Arranging for someone else to deliver them on your behalf.<br />\r\nThe rules require that documents be served at least 5 days before the case management hearing.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Do I Have to Pay Any Fees?</span></span></strong><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">The Federal Court may require payment of fees at various stages, including:<br />\r\n&bull; Filing your application.<br />\r\n&bull; Paying for mediation or hearing fees.<br />\r\n&bull; Paying for each day your case is heard in Court.<br />\r\nIf you cannot afford the fees, you can apply for an exemption or deferral. You may also be required to provide security for costs if there is concern that you may not be able to cover the other party&#39;s costs if you lose.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Can the Court Refuse to Accept Documents for Filing?</span></span></strong><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">The Court may refuse to accept your documents for filing if:<br />\r\n&bull; They are incomplete or not properly signed.<br />\r\n&bull; The document is deemed frivolous or vexatious by a Judicial Registrar.<br />\r\n&bull; The Court has issued a directive not to accept the document.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">How Bansal Lawyers Can Assist with Federal Court Applications</span></span></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">At <strong>Bansal Lawyers</strong>, we provide expert legal services in handling applications to the Federal Court. Our services include:</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Determining whether your case involves a jurisdictional error or legal issue</span></span></strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">: We carefully assess the case to see if it is appropriate to take it to the Federal Court.</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Preparing and filing the application</span></span></strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">: Our team handles the entire application process, ensuring compliance with court procedures and deadlines.</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Representing you in Federal Court hearings</span></span></strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">: If your case proceeds to the Federal Court, we will advocate for your rights, presenting compelling arguments to secure the best outcome for you.</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Federal Court applications in migration matters are highly specialized, and it is crucial to have a lawyer with in-depth experience. <strong>Bansal Lawyers</strong> has a proven track record of successfully handling such complex cases.</span></span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.bansallawyers.com.au/chikweu-v-minister-2024-federal-court-visa-refusal-overturn\" title=\"Chikweu v Minister 2024 – Federal Court Overturns Visa Refusal\">Chikweu v Minister 2024 &ndash; Federal Court Overturns Visa Refusal </a></p>', 'Federal Court Application for visa| Expert legal services in Melbourne', 'At Bansal Lawyers, we provide Expert Legal Services in Melbourne handling applications to the Federal Court.', 'Federal Court migration appeal, judicial review visa case, migration court lawyers, visa decision challenge, legal help for migration cases, Expert Legal Services in Melbourne', NULL, NULL, '2025-01-16 22:37:16', '2025-07-12 15:15:26', 'other', 1),
(29, 'sub', 3, 'Intervenition Orders', 'intervenition-orders', 'Intervenition_Orders_Protecting_Your_Rights_and_Safety.png', 'Intervenition Orders', 1, '<div class=\"content-section\"><!-- Heading of the page included in the content section -->\r\n<h1>Intervenition Orders &ndash; Protecting Your Rights and Safety</h1>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">If you are experiencing domestic violence, harassment, or threats, an <strong>Intervention Order</strong> may be necessary to protect yourself and your loved ones. An Intervention Order is a legal order that can place restrictions on someone who is causing harm or distress to another person. Whether you need to <strong>protect yourself from a partner, family member, or acquaintance</strong>, Bansal Lawyers is here to guide you through the process.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">What is an Intervention Order?</span></span></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">An Intervention Order, also known as a <strong>Protection Order</strong>, is a legal order issued by the court to prevent someone from engaging in certain behaviour that causes harm or intimidation. It can include conditions such as:</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">No contact</span></span></strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\"> with the protected person.</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Exclusion from the home</span></span></strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\"> or certain premises.</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Prohibition of specific behaviours</span></span></strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">, like stalking, threats, or assault.</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">When Can You Apply for an Intervention Order?</span></span></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">You can apply for an Intervention Order if you are experiencing any of the following:</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Physical or emotional abuse</span></span></strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">.</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Threats</span></span></strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\"> of violence.</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Harassment</span></span></strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\"> or <strong>stalking</strong>.</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Damage to property</span></span></strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">.</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Controlling behaviour</span></span></strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">, including restrictions on your freedom.</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">At <strong>Bansal Lawyers</strong>, we work with you to ensure your safety is the priority. Whether you are seeking an <strong>Apprehended Domestic Violence Order (ADVO)</strong> or a <strong>Personal Safety Intervention Order (PSIO)</strong>, we provide expert legal advice and representation to help you secure the protection you need.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">The Court Process for an Intervention Order</span></span></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">The process to obtain an Intervention Order involves:</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Filing an application</span></span></strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\"> at your local court.</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Court hearing</span></span></strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">, where both parties will have the opportunity to present evidence.</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Order granted</span></span></strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\"> if the court believes that the order is necessary to protect your safety.</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">If you need urgent assistance, we can help expedite the process and guide you every step of the way. <strong>Contact us today</strong> for a confidential consultation.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"/khanal-migration-english-language-requirements-covid-19-case-study\">Read about Khanal migration english language requirements covid 19 case study</a></p>', 'Intervention Order Lawyers in Melbourne | Bansal Lawyers', 'If you are experiencing domestic violence, harassment, or threats and are seeking Intervention Order Lawyers in Melbourne, contact Bansal Lawyers for trusted legal support.', 'Intervention order lawyers Melbourne, restraining order legal help, family violence orders, personal safety orders, intervention order defense', NULL, NULL, '2025-01-16 22:46:51', '2025-07-12 15:18:30', 'other', 1),
(30, 'sub', 3, 'Trafic offences', 'trafic-offences', 'Traffic_Offences.png', 'Trafic offences', 1, '<div class=\"content-section\"><!-- Heading of the page included in the content section -->\r\n<h1>Traffic Offences &ndash; Expert Legal Advice for Drivers in Trouble</h1>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Traffic offences can lead to serious consequences, including fines, license suspensions, and even imprisonment in some cases. At <strong>Bansal Lawyers</strong>, we understand how stressful it can be to face charges related to <strong>driving offences</strong>. Whether you&rsquo;re facing charges for speeding, driving without a valid license, or more serious offences like dangerous driving, we offer expert legal support to protect your rights.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Types of Traffic Offences in Australia</span></span></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Traffic offences can be categorized into <strong>minor</strong> and <strong>major</strong> offences. Some common charges include:</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Speeding offences</span></span></strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">: Exceeding the speed limit, including high-range speeding.</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Driving without a valid license</span></span></strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">: Driving when your license is expired, suspended, or disqualified.</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Reckless driving</span></span></strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">: Driving in a manner that endangers the safety of others.</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Driving under the influence of drugs or alcohol</span></span></strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">: A serious offence that can lead to significant penalties.</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Failing to stop after an accident</span></span></strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">: Leaving the scene of a crash without reporting the incident.</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Penalties for Traffic Offences</span></span></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">The penalties for traffic offences vary depending on the severity of the offence and whether any aggravating factors were involved. For example:</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Speeding offences</span></span></strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">: Fines and demerit points.</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Reckless driving</span></span></strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">: Can result in disqualification of your driver&rsquo;s license and heavy fines.</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Driving under the influence (DUI)</span></span></strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">: Possible license suspension, fines, or imprisonment.</span></span><